author: Robert Suhay
title: Football roundup | Booker T. rallies past Churchland
text:
Booker T. Washington 21, Churchland 12 Jamari Logan, a 6-foot-5, 340-pound defensive tackle, rushed for two short-yardage touchdowns and the visiting Bookers (2-3) rallied past the Truckers on Tuesday.
Churchland jumped to a 12-0 lead in the second quarter before Logan scored his first from three yards out. Amir Carter's extra point made it 12-7 at halftime.
Ending a drive that began in the third quarter, the Bookers started the fourth with Logan's second score from four yards out.
Bookers QB Alvonte Lawton found Damian Jiggetts for a 30-yard catch-and-run TD to put the game out of reach.
Bogged down by penalties, which nullified a few big plays in the first half, the Bookers regained discipline in the second half.
First-year coach DJ Alexander told the team to "continue to believe in the game plan, eliminate the penalties and focus on the little things."
____
Wilson 21, Norcom 12
Tramone Harrison recovered a fumble in the end zone in the second quarter and the Presidents (3-2) rallied from an early 6-0 deficit to beat the visiting Greyhounds (0-5).
Norcom's Hadji Macklin returned an interception 50 yards for a touchdown on the fifth play of the game but Wilson soon took over.
Wilson's Aaron Moore rushed for 84 yards and QuaShawn Harrison added 60 more yards on the ground.
Josh Elliot rushed 14 times for 73 yeards for the Greyhounds.
- Reported by Charlie Baumgardner
